Package: cdmt
Type: Package
Title: Change Detection by Multispectral Trends
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Donato", "Morresi", email = "donato.morresi@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3545-872X")),
    person("Hyeyoung", "Maeng", email = "h.maeng4@lancaster.ac.uk", role = "aut"),
    person("Matteo", "Garbarino", email = "matteo.garbarino@unito.it", role = c("ctb", "fnd"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9010-1731"))
    )
Description: Detects changes in linear trends of inter-annual satellite time series (e.g. Landsat time series) using the High-dimensional Trend Segmentation (HiTS) procedure proposed by Maeng (2019).
    Satellite time series can be either univariate or multivariate (i.e. including multiple spectral bands and indices).        
